
Installing JX Memory Debugger:

The program (jx_memory_debugger) should be placed in a directory that is on
your execution path.  /usr/bin or ~/bin are usually good choices.


Running JX Memory Debugger:

If the program crashes or if you find other bugs, please check the web page
first to see if they have already been reported.


Notes on JX Memory Debugger:

jx_memory_debugger displays the memory usage of any program writting using
the JX Application Framework and is very useful for detecting and tracking
down memory leaks.

The main web page for JX is

    https://github.com/jafl/jx_application_framework/

